  "prompt": "How do I survive office politics?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to navigate office politics:\n\n1. Stay professional\n- Avoid gossip\n- Remain neutral\n- Focus on your work performance\n\n2. Build positive relationships\n- Network respectfully\n- Be helpful and collaborative\n- Develop genuine connections\n\n3. Understand the organizational dynamics\n- Learn who has influence\n- Observe workplace power structures\n- Know unwritten rules\n\n4. Communicate effectively\n- Be clear and diplomatic\n- Listen actively\n- Choose your words carefully\n\n5. Maintain boundaries\n- Don't get overly personal\n- Keep emotions in check\n- Avoid taking sides in conflicts\n\n6. Document your achievements\n- Keep track of your contributions\n- Be transparent about your work\n- Highlight your value to the organization\n\n7. Stay ethical\n- Be honest\n- Maintain integrity\n- Don't compromise your principles\n\n8. Develop emotional intelligence\n- Read social cues\n- Manage your reactions\n- Be self-aware\n\n9. Have a mentor or trusted advisor\n- Get guidance\n- Seek objective perspectives\n- Learn from experienced colleagues\n\n10. Know when to escalate issues\n- Address serious problems professionally\n- Use proper channels\n- Seek HR support if necessary\n\nRemember, the goal is to navigate politics without compromising your professional reputation.",
